<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880915-0100 </DOCNO><HL> Credit Ratings: Moody's Raises Rating On Securities of USX And Its Subsidiaries </HL><SO> </SO><CO> X </CO><IN> BON STK FIN </IN><DATELINE> PITTSBURGH  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Moody's Investors Service Inc. raised the ratings on $3.9 billion of securities of USX Corp. and its subsidiaries, citing progress made by the steel and oil producer to reduce its debt.    The credit-rating service also said it expects Pittsburgh-based USX will continue to improve its capital structure, aided by the strong market positions of its core business units.    Among the upgrades, USX's senior notes and debentures, including Eurobonds, and tax-exempt revenue bonds were raised to Baa-3 from Ba-1; its adjustable-rate preferred stock to Ba-1 from Ba-2, and commercial paper to Prime-3 from not prime; senior notes, debentures and tax-exempt issues for its Marathon Oil Co. unit to Baa-3 from Ba-1; first mortgage bonds for the Texas Oil andamp; Gas Corp. unit to Baa-2 from Baa-3, and Texas Oil andamp; Gas's senior notes and debentures to Baa-3 from Ba-1. </TEXT></DOC>